<h1>New diabetes literature just for children</h1>

<h4>10<sup>th</sup> August 2009</h4>


<p class="intro"></p>



	<blockquote><p>A new guide designed specifically for children with diabetes has been launched by BD Medical – Diabetes Care</p></blockquote>


<!-- This is the @content.body with the pullquotes, featureboxes, image and caption added in -->
<div class='article-img'><img src="http://images.scholastic.co.uk/assets/a/ec/53/istock-000008651367medium-313572.jpg" title="Diabetes" alt="Diabetes" /></div>

	<p>New diabetes literature which has been designed specifically for children uses child-friendly language and imagery to simply and clearly explain how best to take blood samples and self-inject insulin. The aim of the guide is primarily to help ensure that children manage their diabetes properly, and remain fit and healthy. The literature is available from diabetes specialist nurses, as well as direct from the company, email bddiabetes@europe.bd.com or call 01865 781666.</p>


	<p>Jazz Panchoo, Business Director, UK and Ireland, BD Medical – Diabetes Care, says, ‘Helping people with diabetes to manage their condition as effectively as possible is critical to managing their quality of life and their long-term health.</p>


	<p>We have recognised that the style and language which appeal to children is not the same as that designed for teenagers, or professionals, or older people. That’s why we have created support literature specifically for different age groups. We hope that this will contribute to a major improvement in injection technique among children and their parents and carers’.</p>







